article.description: Curran Scott had a season-high 23 points as Tulsa defeated East Carolina 91-78 on Sunday.
article.headline: Scott scores 23 to lift Tulsa past East Carolina 91-78
article.linkText: Scott scores 23 to lift Tulsa past East Carolina 91-78
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Curran Scott had a season-high 23 points as Tulsa defeated East Carolina 91-78 on Sunday. Martins Igbanu had 19 points for Tulsa (18-12, 8-9 American Athletic Conference). Jeriah Horne added 17 points. DaQuan Jeffries had seven rebounds for the hosts. Isaac Fleming tied a season high with 20 points plus 10 assists and nine rebounds for the Pirates (10-18, 3-13). Shawn Williams added 18 points. Seth LeDay had 15 points. The Golden Hurricane improve to 2-0 against the Pirates on the season. Tulsa defeated East Carolina 77-73 on Feb. 17. Tulsa finishes out the regular season against Memphis on the road on Saturday. East Carolina plays Wichita State on the road on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
